What is tuple? Difference between list and tuple.

Tuple is also a type of sequence in python. It is ordered and immutable.
Tuple starts with ()

Difference between a list and a tuple is that Lists are mutable(i.e. they can be altered, we
can add or remove elements from a list) but tuples are not mutable, i.e. we can't change 
its stored values directly. Simplest way to do so is to convert a tuple into list.